OL,6,FTELETEXT PEOPLE - GRAHAM LOVELACE      
OL,7, Graham worked at CEEFAX at the         
OL,8, beginning of the 1990s and was given   
OL,9, the opportunity to run a new teletext  
OL,10, service for commercial TV just after   
OL,11, the biggest shake up of television     
OL,12, regulations in the UK at the time.     
OL,14, He explains how he manged to get the   
OL,15, service going and make a success of it,
OL,16, then foresee the trouble coming down   
OL,17, the pipe from non-broadcast competition
OL,18, and the attempts to adapt.             
OL,19, today Graham is a media consultant and 
OL,20, can be reached atCwww.lovelace.co.uk   
